<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN DIEGO EARNINGS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Advanced Marketing Services The San Diego-based supplier of books to the 
discount warehouse industry, including Price Clubs, reported a second-quarter 
profit of $639,000, down 8% from the $693,000 profit the previous year. For the 
six months ended Sept. 30, profit was $827,000, down 32% from the $1.2 million 
net income over the same six months last year. Profits were hurt by lower 
margins and higher administrative expenses, the company said. 
</P>
