EARNINGS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Southwestern Bell Corp.: The St. Louis-based telecommunications company's 
third-quarter net income fell 9% from a year ago to $295.3 million. Revenue 
totaled $2.2 billion, down slightly from last year. The results were attributed 
to a franchise tax refund Southwestern Bell Telephone Co. received last year; 
the shift in production of several Yellow Pages directories from the third to 
the fourth quarters; a one-time adjustment to the telephone company's revenue, 
and a rate refund for Missouri customers as part of an agreement between state 
regulators and the telephone company. The factors came despite growth in the 
telephone company's customer access lines. 
</P>
</TEXT>
