<P>
Seagate Technology Inc.: The Scotts Valley, Calif., maker of disk drives for 
small computer systems reported first-quarter net income of $23.4 million, 
contrasted with the year-ago period's $52.8-million loss that the company 
attributed to overproduction and over-staffing. Net sales increased 25% to 
$378.9 million. 
</P>
