<P>
Coca-Cola Enterprises: The Atlanta bottler said third-quarter profit fell 68.2% 
due to increased marketing costs, reduced sales volume and the repurchase of 
stock. Earnings totaled $12.7 million on revenue of $1.022 billion, compared to 
$39.9 million on revenue of $1.025 billion in the same period a year ago. The 
bottling company, which was spun off from Coca-Cola Co. in 1986, said volume 
fell about 3%, reflecting the sale of the Coca-Cola Bottling Company of 
Mid-America. The firm also repurchased about 1.2 million shares of common stock 
during the quarter. 
</P>
