Manufacturers Hanover Corp.: The New York bank reported a third-quarter loss of 
$789 million, the result of its previously announced decision to add $950 
million to its loan-loss reserves. This contrasts with net income of $198 
million in last year's third quarter. The firm said its 1989 third-quarter net 
income would have totaled $91 million without the one-time writedown. 
</P>
