<P>
Warner-Lambert Co.: The Morris Plains, N.J.-based drug firm's third-quarter 
profit climbed 22% from a year ago to a record $107 million. Sales totaled a 
record $1.11 billion, a gain of 7%. The results were attributed to higher 
worldwide sales of the company's pharmaceuticals, increased sales of 
non-prescription health-care products, including Listerine mouthwash, Halls 
cough tablets, Rolaids antacid, Lubriderm skin lotion and Efferdent denture 
cleaner and added sales of confectionary products led by Trident sugarless gum. 
</P>
