<TEXT>
<P>
Wells Fargo &amp; Co.: The San Francisco banking company's third-quarter 
earnings advanced 17% from a year ago to $153.7 million. The provision for loan 
losses was $82 million, up 9%. The results were attributed in part to the solid 
performance of the state's economy and its move to bolster its presence in 
Southern California. During the period, the firm signed definitive agreements 
to buy Valley National Bank of Glendale, Central Pacific Corp. of Bakersfield 
and Torrey Pines Group of Solana Beach. 
</P>
