<HEADLINE>
<P>
MORNING REPORT: MOVIES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By STEVE WEINSTEIN, Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Mikis Theodorakis, a former Communist member of the Greek Parliament and the 
composer of the music for the movie "Zorba the Greek," says he's going to run 
for Parliament again, this time on a conservative party ticket. Theodorakis 
resigned his seat in 1986 after 4 1/2 years in office, complaining that his 
presence there had become pointless. He said the turnabout was prompted by the 
slaying of Pavlos Bakoyannis, the spokesman for the New Democracy Party, by the 
extreme left-wing November 17 guerrilla organization.STEVE WEINSTEIN 
</P>
</TEXT>
