</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Convention on International Trade in Endangered Species, meeting in 
Lausanne, Switzerland, approved a formal ban on trading in ivory. The action 
followed a resolution to the same effect the day before. Several southern 
African nations that contend they protect their elephants and need ivory 
revenue hinted that they may bypass the ban. There are about 600,000 elephants 
left in Africa, only about half the total of 10 years ago. 
