<P>
President Mikhail S. Gorbachev reportedly stunned reformers by harshly 
criticizing historian Yuri N. Afanasyev, a key leader of radical forces, at a 
closed meeting with top editors last week. Gorbachev also attacked a poll that 
ranked physicist Andrei D. Sakharov as the most popular member of the new 
