said. Gorbachev called Afanasyev's recent speeches incompatible with his party 
membership, suggesting that he should quit or be expelled, they said. And he 
told Vladislav A. Starkov, the editor the country's most popular periodical, 
that as a result of publication of the Sakharov poll, he should considering 
resigning, they said. 
