</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Eric Dickerson intends to fulfill his contract with the Indianapolis Colts but 
says he may retire when it expires after the 1990 season. 
</P>
<P>
"Football is a sport that takes a lot out of you mentally and physically," 
Dickerson said on a television talk show. "After this season, I have one year 
left. I'll play that for sure. But even if they offered me a new contract, I 
don't think I'd sign it right now." 
