<HEADLINE>
<P>
LOCAL; 
</P>
<P>
FOG SHUTS JOHN WAYNE AIRPORT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times staff and wire service reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
For the second morning in a row, Orange County's John Wayne Airport was closed 
because of fog until 8:45 a.m. today, airport officials said. 
</P>
<P>
The closure compounded problems that started when the airport was closed 
because of limited visibility starting at 6:50 p.m. Tuesday, which remained in 
effect all night, Assistant Airport Manager Jan Mittermeier said. 
</P>
<P>
But because of the closure Tuesday evening, only about three aircraft remained 
grounded by morning today, Mittermeier added. "We didn't have a mess as far as 
the planes trying to get out of here because none were on the ground," 
Mittermeier said. 
</P>
<P>
Airport operations were also halted Tuesday morning until 10 a.m. because of 
fog. 
</P>
</TEXT>
