<P>
CHICAGO GETS AN EARLY SNOW 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times wire services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Snow fell in Chicago as the mercury plunged 20 degrees below normal in the 
Midwest and Plains early today, while cool air mixed with scattered rain over 
much of the Atlantic Coast and southern United States. 
</P>
<P>
The National Weather Service issued flood warnings in Jackson, Ky., after the 
Kentucky River overflowed onto local roads. There were no reports of injuries, 
the weather service said. 
</P>
<P>
The Chicago area's first snow of the season fell this morning, about two weeks 
earlier than normal, forecasters said. Light snow fell at 6:07 a.m. at O'Hare 
International Airport, forecaster Frank Wachowski said. 
</P>
